<sect1 id="star" xreflabel="star from schilytools-&schilytools-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="star.html"?>


  <title>star from schilytools-&schilytools-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="star">
    <primary sortas="a-star">star</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to star from schilytools</title>

    <para>
      Due to various upstream-acknowledged issues in heirloom-ng tar, it is
      preferred to use a different SVR4-compatible tar implementation. This
      package is exactly that.
    </para>

    &long-build-time;

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download: <ulink url="&schilytools-download;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of star from schilytools</title>

    <para>
      First build <command>smake</command> to allow overriding variables in
      build files:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>pushd psmake &amp;&amp;
  sh MAKE-all &amp;&amp;
popd</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Compile star by running the following
      commands, and ensure an older GNU standard is used:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>psmake/smake -e CC="cc -std=gnu17"</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user, install star and the
      supplementary tools:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>install -vDm755 star/OBJ/*/star         \
                star_sym/OBJ/*/star_sym \
                tartest/OBJ/*/tartest   \
        -t /usr/5bin/ &amp;&amp;
install -vDm644 star/star.1             \
                star_sym/star_sym.1     \
                tartest/tartest.1       \
        -t /usr/share/man/5man/man1/</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

